Τ110 subject here seems to be the rule vitiis nemo sine (as in υ. 68.), and the deductione from it; e. 9. that the observation of faults in others should remind ns of our own3 that the best construction should be put upon each other’s actions; and that censures, where there is call for them, should be modified and discriminating.
